title: Production of argon isotopes by spallation of Sc,Ti, Fe,Co,Ni and Cu

x4freetext: Production of argon isotopes by spallation of Sc,Ti,
Fe,Co,Ni and Cu

x4codes.hlp: Centre d`Etudes Nucleaires de Bordeaux-Gradignan, France

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.20, p.1517 (1979)

x4freetext: The targets consisted of stacks of 20*20 mm squares of
metal foil of thickness 0.010 to 0.050 mm. Al foil was
inserted between the target foils (Sc,Ti,V,Fe,Co,Ni
and Cu) to serve as guards, recoil collectors and
monitors. The thicknesses of the stacks were
0.15 g/cm2 for the irradiation at 0.080 GeV, 0.3 to
0.5 g/cm2 at 0.15,0.6, and 24 GeV,and 1.5 g/cm2 at
1.05 GeV. Each target contained either 3 to 6 monitors.
Semiempirical fits.
The integrated flux employed varied from 0.5 to
5 x 10**17 protons.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Centre d`Etudes Nucleaires, note, No.1466(1) (1971)

x4freetext: The argon samples were analyzed in a 60 degree
sector,12 cm radius mass spectrometer (a modified
micromass-12).

/By authors/ In general, each target element was
subjected to three independent irradiations at each
energy E(p) and two years,at least, elapsed between
irradiation and analysis.
